&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Academy Athletic Trainer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Medical&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to:&lt;/strong&gt; Director of Performance Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FC Cincinnati is searching for an experienced, reliable, and detail-oriented Academy Athletic Trainer. The Developmental Academy Athletic Trainer will be responsible for, but not limited to implementing the sports medicine program and coordinating medical care for the development academy.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The ideal candidate must be self-motivated, detailed- oriented, professional, possess strong communication skills and the ability to work in a fast-paced environment. This position is employed by FC Cincinnati and reports to the Director of Performance Services.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluation, treatment, and rehab of Academy players under the supervision of team Chief Medical Officer and Director of Performance Services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with medical staff, coaches, family members, and athletes&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refer athletes to team physicians or other health care providers when necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with practice and game coverage including travel (could include travel outside of the United States)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the Performance Department in planning, delivering, and evaluating physical development sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain computerized injury and treatment logs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparation of field and team for practices and games, including but not limited to preparing coolers/ice chest, placement of emergency equipment and medical prepartions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep athletic training room clean, organized, and safe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preceptor responsibilities with local athletic training residents and students&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comply with all company and league medical policies and protocols&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned or required&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or Masters Degree in athletic training from CAATE recognized school required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NATABOC Certification required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Ohio Athletic Trainer Licensure required or the ability to obtain quickly&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current Professional CPR Certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must pass a background check to work with minors. Must undergo mandatory Safe Sport online training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certified Strength &amp;amp; Conditioning Coach (CSCS) preferred&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;What You’ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Positive upbeat attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently, with minimal supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work long, irregular hours and weekends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to communicate well with coaching staff and other members of the club&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work on a team to accomplish common goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle confidential information in a respectful and appropriate manner&lt;/li&gt;
