&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Academy Director&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Academy- Technical&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to: &lt;/strong&gt;General Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Academy Director will lead all aspects of FC Cincinnati’s Academy program and oversee the daily sporting and administrative operations of the Academy. Reporting to the Director of Player Development, this individual will be responsible for building an elite developmental environment that prepares players for progression into FC Cincinnati 2 and ultimately the First Team. The Academy Director will also play a key leadership role in coach education, staffing, talent identification, and the long-term strategic growth of the Academy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage the day-to-day sporting and administrative operations of the FC Cincinnati Academy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and maintain the Club’s player development methodology and game model consistently across all Academy age groups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee curriculum planning, training periodization, and competition schedules to ensure age-appropriate development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with the Director of Player Development, FC Cincinnati 2 staff, and First Team technical staff to maintain a consistent player development pathway.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the Academy coaching staff, including hiring, mentorship, evaluation, and ongoing professional development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain a comprehensive coach education program that reinforces the Club’s playing philosophy, training standards, and developmental expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain high performance standards and accountability across all Academy teams and staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support player identification and recruitment efforts throughout the local, regional, national, and international youth markets as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear and consistent communication with players, parents, coaches, and internal stakeholders regarding Academy standards and expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with MLS, MLS NEXT, U.S. Soccer, SafeSport, and all other governing body regulations and standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent FC Cincinnati and the Academy in a professional manner within the local community and broader soccer landscape&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete proficiency in the use of the Microsoft Office including Excel, Word, Outlook, and PowerPoint&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be willing to work nights, weekends and holidays, and be prepared for extensive travel for preseason, away games, post-season trips, et cetera&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have excellent interpersonal written/verbal communication skills, be detail-oriented and highly organized with the ability to simultaneously handle multiple tasks and adapt to change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to create and maintain effective relationships with parents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively recruit players and their families to Cincinnati&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current expertise in U.S. and world soccer from the Academy to the 1st Team level, and a willingness to continue to learn best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent FCC in a professional manner at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What You’ll Bring:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;USSF “A” coaching license or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree from a 4 year university and/or have been a professional soccer player at a country’s highest level for at least 5 years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 7 yea

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Academy Driver&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Academy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to: &lt;/strong&gt;Manager, Academy Player Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part-Time Driver for FC Cincinnati Academy to transport Academy players to and potentially from soccer training. The candidate will be responsible for the safety and well-being of children during transportation, follow the provided schedule of pick up and drop off times, and maintain a professional and courteous environment and demeanor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely transport Academy players (minors) to and potentially from soccer training according to daily schedule provided.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the safety and well-being of all passengers during transit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain punctuality for all pick-up and drop-off times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow all traffic laws and regulations to ensure safe driving practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform pre-trip and post-trip vehicle inspections to ensure the company vehicle is in good working condition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with FC Cincinnati Staff and other stakeholders regarding transportation logistics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep accurate records of trips, including mileage and times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the cleanliness and upkeep of the company vehicle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report any incidents or accidents to the appropriate authorities and company management immediately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work flexible hours including early mornings, evenings, weekends, and varying hours based on soccer training schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to remain calm and focused during stressful situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Punctual, reliable, and trustworthy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to pass a background check and drug screening.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with SafeSport.&lt;/li&gt;
